result.name: Lo Chiu Vietnamese Restaurant

reviews.text: Fantastic food. I live nearby and find myself eating here at least once a week due to the high-quality food and fantastic value. I usually order the beef or chicken pho, which is the best I've had outside of Vietnam. The fresh spring rolls are also really good, they use fresh juicy shrimp and Vietnamese sausage as filling. The set menu is also very good value and is very filling and varied.
Great as always. Ordered the fried soft crab, and the crab meat tomato soup noodle.

Delicious Vietnam food with quality and quantity.
The satay beef rice noodle was a must try dish!
Good food. Service could be better

We liked the food, specially the Pho at Lo Chiu. Each was about 60 HKD but quite good. Unfortunately, they missed one order but over all the waiter was nice and his english was better than expected.

Very unfortunate we found this place only two days before we leave Hongkong.

We like it better than the DimSum close to this place.

reviews.text: 廣告效應，米之蓮根本就是十分難吃。味道相比五年前差得遠。現在是從中央工場交來的，所以根本就是一個局
服務一般。食物中下，经理員工無招呼。

Fantastic food. I live nearby and find myself eating here at least once a week due to the high-quality food and fantastic value. I usually order the beef or chicken pho, which is the best I've had outside of Vietnam. The fresh spring rolls are also really good, they use fresh juicy shrimp and Vietnamese sausage as filling. The set menu is also very good value and is very filling and varied.
味道很好，份量較少，在附近經過的話值得一去
